Answer:
Here is a structured answer that directly addresses the question, covering all critical regulatory obligations and avoiding any contradictions:

To ensure compliance with Rules 12.12.1(1) to 12.12.1(7), changes or additions to previously disclosed information about Petroleum Reserves should be documented as follows:

* The disclosure must contain the types of permits or licences held by the Petroleum Reporting Entity relating to the estimates (Rule 12.6.1(1));
* An explanation of the new data and information that has affected the estimates of Petroleum Reserves must be provided (Rule 12.6.1(2));
* The disclosure must include an explanation of how the new data and information has affected the estimates of Petroleum Reserves (Rule 12.6.1(3));
* Any changes or additions to the information previously disclosed relating to Petroleum Reserves under Rules 12.12.1(1) to 12.12.1(7) must be disclosed (Rule 12.6.1(4)(c));
* The disclosure must be made by a Competent Person, who must ensure that the disclosure contains all required information and meets the substance requirements of Authorised Persons (Rule 11.12.2);
* The Petroleum Reporting Entity must commit resources to operate effectively as an Authorised Person within ADGM, including substantive resources committed within ADGM across all lines of the Authorised Person's activities (FSRA Guidance on Spot Commodities Framework);
* The Petroleum Reporting Entity must adhere to the FSRA's Anti-Money Laundering and Countering Financing of Terrorism ("AML/CFT") framework at all times and put the appropriate measures in place to mitigate these risks (FSRA AML and Sanctions Rules and Guidance);
* The Petroleum Reporting Entity must comply with UAE AML/CFT Federal Laws, including the UAE Cabinet Resolution No. (38) of 2014 Concerning the Executive Regulation of the Federal Law No. 4 of 2002 concerning Anti-Money Laundering and Combating Terrorism Financing (FSRA AML and Sanctions Rules and Guidance);
* The Petroleum Reporting Entity must adopt international best practices, including FATF Recommendations, and monitor national and international sanctions lists (FSRA AML and Sanctions Rules and Guidance).

By following these requirements, a Petroleum Reporting Entity can ensure that changes or additions to previously disclosed information about Petroleum Reserves are documented in compliance with Rules 12.12.1(1) to 12.12.1(7) and meet all relevant regulatory obligations.

