Our firm conducts a Targeted Financial Sanctions (TFS) risk assessment as a separate and distinct element of its business risk assessment, in order to identify, understand, assess, and mitigate TFS risks. This includes conducting a proliferation financing and terrorist financing risk assessment.

In conducting the TFS risk assessment, we take into account our business activities, products, and services, as well as our customers, counterparties, and geographic locations. We assess the risks associated with each of these factors and evaluate the likelihood and potential impact of each risk.

Our TFS risk assessment includes the following measures:

* Identifying high-risk customers, countries, and industries that may be subject to sanctions or have links to proliferation financing or terrorist financing;
* Implementing policies and procedures to prevent and detect suspicious transactions and activities;
* Conducting due diligence on customers, counterparties, and agents to ensure they are not subject to sanctions or involved in proliferation financing or terrorist financing;
* Monitoring transactions and activities for signs of suspicious behavior;
* Reporting suspicious transactions and activities to the relevant authorities;
* Implementing measures to prevent the use of shell companies, trusts, or other legal entities to conceal beneficial ownership or facilitate illegal activities;
* Training employees on TFS risks and the importance of compliance;
* Conducting regular reviews and updates of our TFS risk assessment and policies.

To address proliferation financing and terrorist financing risks, we have implemented the following measures:

* Conducting enhanced due diligence on high-risk customers and counterparties;
* Implementing additional monitoring and screening procedures to detect suspicious transactions and activities;
* Restricting or prohibiting transactions with countries, entities, or individuals subject to sanctions;
* Implementing strict anti-bribery and corruption policies and procedures;
* Conducting regular training and awareness programs for employees on proliferation financing and terrorist financing risks.

Our systems and controls are designed to ensure compliance with Federal AML Legislation, AML Rulebook, and other relevant regulations. We have established policies and procedures to prevent money laundering, terrorist financing, and proliferation financing, and to report suspicious transactions and activities to the relevant authorities.

We also have in place procedures to ensure that we are aware of any money laundering or sanctions matters that could result in adverse reputational consequences to the firm. This includes having a whistleblower policy and procedure, as well as regular audits and reviews of our AML/TFS policies and procedures.

Furthermore, we have a third-party audit obligation to verify that the amount and value of client assets held on custody on behalf of clients is correct and matches what the Virtual Asset Custodian is supposed to hold.

Overall, our firm is committed to complying with all applicable AML/TFS regulations and implementing effective measures to prevent and detect money laundering, terrorist financing, and proliferation financing.

