Conflicts of Interest: For the purposes of identifying the types of conflict of interest that arise, or may arise, in the course of providing a service and whose existence may entail a material risk of damage to the interests of a Client, an Authorised Person must take into account, as a minimum, whether the Authorised Person or a person directly or indirectly linked by control to the Authorised Person:
(1)	is likely to make a financial gain, or avoid a financial loss, at the expense of the Client;
(2)	has an interest in the outcome of a service provided to the Client or of a Transaction carried out on behalf of the Client, which is distinct from the Client's interest in that outcome;
