To constitute a "credible net zero emissions target and strategy," an Authorised Person must include the following items in its internal reporting of Operational Risks:

* Monitor results (item a);
* Assess Operational Risk framework performed by control functions (item b);
* Reports generated by/supervisory authorities (item c);
* Material breaches of risk appetite and tolerance (item d);
* Significant internal Operational Risk events and losses (item e);
* Relevant external events and potential impact on Operational Risk framework (item f).

In addition, an Authorised Person's net zero emissions target and strategy must be aligned with its anti-money laundering, financial crime, and know-your-customer obligations under the Virtual Asset Framework. This includes the use of technology solutions to track Virtual Assets, ensuring that the source and destination of these assets can be accurately identified.

To reasonably validate that an entity is on course to meet its net zero emissions targets, an Authorised Person must:

1. Ensure that risk management systems enable implementation of the Operational Risk policy (Section a, An Authorised Person must);
2. Identify, assess, mitigate, control, and monitor risk (Section b, An Authorised Person must);
3. Review and update the policy at intervals appropriate to the nature, scale, and complexity of activities (Section c, An Authorised Person must);
4. Establish and maintain effective policies, procedures, systems, and controls to prevent money laundering (Section a, A Relevant Person must);
5. Ensure that systems and controls enable regular management information to be provided to senior management on the operation and effectiveness of AML/TFS systems and controls (Section b(i), A Relevant Person must);
6. Ensure that systems and controls enable determination of whether a customer or beneficial owner is a Politically Exposed Person (PEP), and compliance with the Rules and Federal AML Legislation (Section b(ii-iii), A Relevant Person must);
7. Ensure that regular risk assessments are carried out to ensure the adequacy of AML/TFS systems and controls (Section c, A Relevant Person must);
8. Maintain clear policies and procedures to identify the source of funds and ensure compliance with COBS Rules (Section 17.5(c) and (e) An Authorised Person must);
9. Have sufficient professional indemnity insurance coverage to reimburse customers in the event of operational risk events (Rule 6.12A.2);
10. Include exposures associated with high risks in its risk assessment, such as investments in venture capital funds, hedge funds, speculative immovable property financing, and Investments declared by the Regulator to constitute high risk (Rule 4.12.19);
11. Ensure that oversight arrangements include the powers and duties of persons appointed to provide the oversight function, including the Licensed Partner function for a Partnership established under the Limited Liability Partnership Regulations or the Partnership Act (This Rule sets out the general requirements relating to the oversight arrangements which a Public Fund must have).

By including these items in its internal reporting and adhering to these regulatory requirements, an Authorised Person can reasonably validate that an entity is on course to meet its net zero emissions targets and strategy.

